[{"location":"#TsyganenkoModels","page":"Home","title":"TsyganenkoModels","text":"Modeling of Earth's Magnetosphere Using Spacecraft Magnetometer Data.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"Magnetic field model (native Julia implementations)\n[x] Supported models: T89, T96\n[x] T01/T02: A model of the near magnetosphere with a dawn-dusk asymmetry\n\nnote: IRBEM.jl\nIRBEM.jl is a Julia wrapper for the IRBEM Fortran library that exposes magnetic field computation via GET_FIELD_MULTI and supports more Tsyganenko models, but may be outdated and slower than the native Julia implementations.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"TsyganenkoModels\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quickstart","page":"Home","title":"Quickstart","text":"using TsyganenkoModels\nusing Dates\n\nt = DateTime(\"1970-01-01T00:01:40\")\nð« = [1, 2, 3]\niopt = 2\ndb_jl_t = t89(ð«, t, iopt)\n\npdyn = 2.0   # Solar wind dynamic pressure [nPa]\ndst = -87.0  # Dst index [nT]\nbyimf = 2.0  # IMF By [nT]\nbzimf = -5.0 # IMF Bz [nT]\nps = -0.533585131\nresult_t01 = t01(ð«, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf)\nresult_t01 = t96(ð«, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Comparison-with-[geopack](https://github.com/tsssss/geopack)","page":"Home","title":"Comparison with geopack","text":"using TsyganenkoModels\nusing GeoCotrans\nusing Test\nusing Geopack\nusing Dates\n\nt = DateTime(\"1970-01-01T00:01:40\")\nð« = [1, 2, 3]\n\n# using geopack\nxgsm, ygsm, zgsm = ð«\nut = datetime2unix(t)    # 1970-01-01/00:01:40 UT.\nps = Geopack.recalc(ut)\ndb_py = Geopack.t89(2, ps, xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\n\n# using TsyganenkoModels\ndb_jl = t89(ð«, ps, 2)\n\n@test db_py == db_jl","category":"section"},{"location":"#Model-Result-Comparison","page":"Home","title":"Model Result Comparison","text":"# T01 model comparison\npdyn = 2.0   # Solar wind dynamic pressure [nPa]\ndst = -87.0  # Dst index [nT]\nbyimf = 2.0  # IMF By [nT]\nbzimf = -5.0 # IMF Bz [nT]\ng1 = 0.0\ng2 = 0.0\nparmod = [pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf, g1, g2]\n\ndb_t96_py = Geopack.t96(parmod, ps, xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\ndb_t96_jl = t96(ð«, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf)\n@test collect(db_t96_jl) â‰ˆ db_t96_py rtol = 1e-6\n\ndb_t01_py = Geopack.t01(parmod, ps, xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\ndb_t01_jl = t01(ð«, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf; g1, g2)\n\n@test collect(db_t01_jl) â‰ˆ db_t01_py rtol = 1e-6\n\nThe internal magnetic field could be computed using igrf from GeoCotrans.\n\nHere we verify the result with igrf_gsm from Geopack.\n\nusing GeoCotrans\n\nb0_py = Geopack.igrf_gsm(xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\nb0_jl = GeoCotrans.igrf(GSM(ð«) .* GeoCotrans.RðŸœ¨, t)\n@test b0_jl â‰ˆ b0_py rtol = 1e-5\n@test GeoCotrans.get_igrf_coeffs(t)[1] â‰ˆ Geopack.load_igrf(ut)[1]","category":"section"},{"location":"#Performance-Benchmarks","page":"Home","title":"Performance Benchmarks","text":"using Chairmarks\n@b TsyganenkoModels.t89(ð«, ps, 2), Geopack.t89(2, ps, xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\n@b TsyganenkoModels.t01(ð«, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf), Geopack.t01([pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf, 0, 0], ps, xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)\n@b GeoCotrans.igrf(GSM(xgsm, ygsm, zgsm) .* GeoCotrans.RðŸœ¨, t), Geopack.igrf_gsm(xgsm, ygsm, zgsm)","category":"section"},{"location":"#API","page":"Home","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#TsyganenkoModels.dipole_tilt-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"TsyganenkoModels.dipole_tilt","text":"dipole_tilt(time) -> Ïˆ\n\nCompute the dipole tilt angle Ïˆ (radians): Ïˆ = asin(áº‘dipole Â· xÌ‚sun).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#TsyganenkoModels.t01-NTuple{8, Any}","page":"Home","title":"TsyganenkoModels.t01","text":"t01(x, y, z, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf; g1 = 0.0, g2 = 0.0) -> (Bx, By, Bz)\n\nCompute GSM components of the external magnetic field using the Tsyganenko 01 model.\n\nParameters\n\nx, y, z: Position in GSM coordinates [Earth radii]\nps: Geodipole tilt angle [radians]\npdyn: Solar wind dynamic pressure [nPa]\ndst: Dst index [nT]\nbyimf: IMF By component [nT]\nbzimf: IMF Bz component [nT]\ng1: G1 index (see Tsyganenko 2001 for definition)\ng2: G2 index (see Tsyganenko 2001 for definition)\n\nReturns\n\n(Bx, By, Bz): Magnetic field components in GSM coordinates [nT]\n\nModel Description\n\nData-based model of the external magnetospheric magnetic field, calibrated by:\n\nSolar wind pressure PDYN (nanopascals)\nDst (nanotesla)\nIMF By and Bz (nanotesla)\nG1 and G2 indices\n\nATTENTION: The model is based on data taken sunward from X=-15 Re, and hence becomes invalid at larger tailward distances.\n\nReferences\n\nTsyganenko, N.A., JGR, 2002\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#TsyganenkoModels.t89-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"Home","title":"TsyganenkoModels.t89","text":"t89(ð«, ps, iopt; cache=nothing) -> GSM(Bx, By, Bz)\nt89(x, y, z, ps, iopt)\nt89(x, y, z, t::AbstractTime, iopt)\n\nCompute GSM components of the magnetic field [nT] produced by extraterrestrial current systems in the geomagnetosphere using the Tsyganenko 89 model, given the position ð« or x, y, z in GSM coordinates [Earth radii], the geodipole tilt angle ps [radians] / time t.\n\nParameters\n\niopt: Ground disturbance level index (1-7)\n1: Kp = 0, 0+\n2: Kp = 1-, 1, 1+\n3: Kp = 2-, 2, 2+\n4: Kp = 3-, 3, 3+\n5: Kp = 4-, 4, 4+\n6: Kp = 5-, 5, 5+\n7: Kp â‰¥ 6-\n\nModel Description\n\nValid up to geocentric distances of 70 RE. Based on merged IMP-A through J (1966-1974), HEOS-1 and -2 (1969-1974), and ISEE-1 and -2 spacecraft data.\n\nReferences\n\nTsyganenko, N.A., \"A magnetospheric magnetic field model with a warped tail current sheet\", Planet. Space Sci., 37, 5-20, 1989.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#TsyganenkoModels.t96-NTuple{8, Any}","page":"Home","title":"TsyganenkoModels.t96","text":"t96(x, y, z, ps, pdyn, dst, byimf, bzimf) -> (Bx, By, Bz)\n\nCompute GSM components of the external magnetic field using the Tsyganenko 96 model.\n\nParameters\n\nx, y, z: Position in GSM coordinates [Earth radii]\nps: Geodipole tilt angle [radians]\npdyn: Solar wind dynamic pressure [nPa]\ndst: Dst index [nT]\nbyimf: IMF By component [nT]\nbzimf: IMF Bz component [nT]\n\nReturns\n\n(Bx, By, Bz): Magnetic field components in GSM coordinates [nT]\n\nModel Description\n\nData-based model calibrated by solar wind pressure, Dst index, and IMF By/Bz components. Includes realistic magnetopause, Region 1 and 2 Birkeland current systems, and IMF penetration.\n\nValid parameter ranges (caution needed outside these ranges):\n\nPdyn: 0.5 to 10 nPa\nDst: -100 to +20 nT\nByIMF and BzIMF: -10 to +10 nT\n\nReferences\n\nTsyganenko & Stern, JGR, v.101, p.27187-27198, 1996\nTsyganenko, JGR, v.100, p.5599-5612, 1995\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
